---
import BaseLayout from "../../layout/BaseLayout.astro";
import HabitatOSCallout from "../../components/habitat-os-callout.astro";

const mailto = "mailto:hey@thefocus.ai?subject=Hiring%20Pipeline%20-%20Assessment%20%26%20Roadmap";
---

<BaseLayout
  pageTitle="AI-Powered Hiring Pipeline | TheFocus.AI"
  description="Stop losing candidates to your own process. We formalize the tribal knowledge in your hiring workflow and build AI systems that keep candidates moving from intake to onboarded."
  category="capabilities"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="py-8 md:py-16">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-graphite border border-ink/15 px-2 py-1 rounded">L1 &rarr; L2</span>
        <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-petrol font-medium">Process Audit & Formalization</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 text-ink leading-tight">
        Stop losing candidates to your own process
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-graphite leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-3xl">
        Your hiring process has more handoffs than your product pipeline. Intake forms are inconsistent, screening criteria live in the hiring manager's head, and the gap between "offer accepted" and "fully onboarded" is where context goes to die.
      </p>
      <a
        href={mailto}
        class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-petrol text-paper font-medium uppercase text-sm tracking-wider rounded-full hover:bg-petrol/90 hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-200"
      >
        Discuss Your Hiring Process &rarr;
      </a>
    </section>

    <!-- Video (disabled for now)
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="relative aspect-video rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <video
          autoplay
          muted
          playsinline
          class="w-full h-full object-cover"
          poster="/videos/offerings/hiring-pipeline.mp4#t=0.1"
        >
          <source src="/videos/offerings/hiring-pipeline.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
        </video>
      </div>
    </section>
    -->

    <!-- The Pain -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-petrol mb-6 font-medium">The Problem</h2>
      <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-ink mb-8">Sound familiar?</h3>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start p-4 rounded-xl bg-tint-warm/30">
          <span class="text-vermilion font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">&times;</span>
          <p class="text-graphite">Every hiring manager writes job descriptions from scratch — or worse, copy-pastes old ones that no longer reflect the role.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start p-4 rounded-xl bg-tint-warm/30">
          <span class="text-vermilion font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">&times;</span>
          <p class="text-graphite">Screening criteria for "good fit" live entirely in the hiring manager's head. When they're out, the recruiter guesses.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start p-4 rounded-xl bg-tint-warm/30">
          <span class="text-vermilion font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">&times;</span>
          <p class="text-graphite">The handoff from recruiter to hiring manager to HR to IT is a chain of emails where context evaporates at every step.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4 items-start p-4 rounded-xl bg-tint-warm/30">
          <span class="text-vermilion font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">&times;</span>
          <p class="text-graphite">Onboarding touches 6+ systems — payroll, benefits, equipment, access provisioning — and nobody owns the full checklist. Things fall through the cracks every single time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Approach -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-petrol bg-paper rounded-r-2xl p-6 md:p-8 shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 mb-4 flex-wrap">
          <h2 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-petrol font-medium">Our Approach</h2>
          <HabitatOSCallout />
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-ink mb-4">How we fix this</h3>
        <p class="text-graphite leading-relaxed mb-6">
          We build a hiring-pipeline Habitat — a system that captures what "good" looks like for each role, structures the intake-to-onboarded workflow, and ensures nothing falls through the handoff chain. The tribal knowledge about screening, culture fit, and onboarding steps gets formalized into a system that runs consistently regardless of who's involved.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-petrol/10 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-sm font-mono font-bold text-petrol">1</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-ink mb-1">Discover</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-graphite">We map your actual hiring workflow — every handoff, every system, every place where tribal knowledge fills the gap. We interview hiring managers to extract what "good" really means for each role.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-petrol/10 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-sm font-mono font-bold text-petrol">2</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-ink mb-1">Structure</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-graphite">Role requirements, screening criteria, and onboarding checklists get formalized into structured templates. The handoff chain gets defined with clear triggers and accountability.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-petrol/10 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-sm font-mono font-bold text-petrol">3</span>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-ink mb-1">Build</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-graphite">An AI system that generates consistent job descriptions from role templates, screens candidates against formalized criteria, orchestrates the handoff chain, and drives onboarding to completion across every system it touches.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Proof Points -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-petrol mb-6 font-medium">Proof</h2>
      <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-ink mb-8">We've done this before</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <a href="/case-study/ai-back-office" class="group block border border-ink/10 rounded-2xl p-6 hover:border-petrol/30 transition-all">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-petrol mb-2">10+ hrs</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-ink mb-2">of weekly back-office work replaced by 6 commands</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-graphite mb-3">AI Back Office — hiring, invoicing, CRM, and communications run through structured AI commands instead of manual processes. Every interaction teaches the system.</p>
          <span class="text-petrol text-sm font-medium group-hover:underline">Read case study &rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/case-study/onboarding" class="group block border border-ink/10 rounded-2xl p-6 hover:border-petrol/30 transition-all">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-petrol mb-2">15 min &rarr; 30 sec</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-ink mb-2">benefits document extraction time</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-graphite mb-3">Onboarding — complex benefits and SBC documents extracted against a unified schema, cutting manual data entry from the new-hire setup process.</p>
          <span class="text-petrol text-sm font-medium group-hover:underline">Read case study &rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Offerings -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-graphite/60 mb-4 font-medium">Related Offerings</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        <a href="/offerings/customer-onboarding" class="group flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl border border-ink/8 hover:border-petrol/30 hover:bg-tint-cool/20 transition-all">
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold text-ink group-hover:text-petrol transition-colors">Customer Onboarding</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-graphite">Formalize the cross-team handoff chain</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-petrol/40 group-hover:text-petrol transition-colors flex-shrink-0">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/offerings/monthly-close" class="group flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl border border-ink/8 hover:border-petrol/30 hover:bg-tint-cool/20 transition-all">
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold text-ink group-hover:text-petrol transition-colors">Monthly Close</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-graphite">Stop the 10-day scramble</p>
          </div>
          <span class="text-petrol/40 group-hover:text-petrol transition-colors flex-shrink-0">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="border-t border-ink/10 pt-16 pb-8">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono text-graphite border border-ink/15 px-2 py-1 rounded">Assessment & Roadmap</span>
        <span class="text-xs font-medium text-graphite">1-2 weeks</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-ink">Ready to stop losing candidates to process?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-graphite mb-8 max-w-2xl">
        The conversation starts with mapping your actual hiring workflow — every handoff, every system, every gap where tribal knowledge fills in.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a
          href={mailto}
          class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-petrol text-paper font-medium uppercase text-sm tracking-wider rounded-full hover:bg-petrol/90 hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-200 text-center"
        >
          Talk to a principal
        </a>
        <a
          href="/capabilities"
          class="inline-block px-8 py-4 border-2 border-ink/20 text-ink font-medium uppercase text-sm tracking-wider rounded-full hover:border-petrol hover:text-petrol hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-200 text-center"
        >
          See the Full Framework
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
